-- Bolshoi Star Questioned as Witness in Acid Attack, Police Say
-- B y   S t e p a n   K r a v c h e n k o
-- 2013-01-25T10:35:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-25/bolshoi-star-questioned-as-witness-in-acid-attack-police-say.html
Bolshoi ballet principal dancer
 Nikolai Tsiskaridze  was questioned two days ago as a witness
after an acid attack on the theater’s artistic director  Sergei
Filin , Moscow police said.  Investigators have also spoken with other employees of the
Bolshoi Theater as well as Filin’s relatives and acquintances,
Alexei Shapkin, a spokesman for the city’s police, said by phone
today.  Filin, a former star dancer at the ballet company, was
attacked with acid outside his home in the Russian capital on
Jan. 17, an assault that police and colleagues said may be
linked to his work.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stepan Kravchenko in Moscow at 
 skravchenko@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
